{"/service/ndnp/mthi/batch_mthi_ivy_ver01/data/sn83004278/00340581970/1957121901/0845.xml":{"full_text":"THE SIDNEY HERALD\nThursday. Dec. 19, 1957\n2\nC Jltt Sidney Jderafd\nC. R- HURLT\nEditor and Publisher\nOFFICIAL NTtWSPAPER OF\nRICHLAVD COUNTY. MONTANA\nNATIONAL EDITORIAL\nA S Tb C\u00dc\u00c4 T I*\u00a9 N\nU\nnMIJH.'U'H'IMf\nWE\nEnter\u00ab! at Uve Pastoffice at Sidney,\nMontana, aa Second Class Matter Marcb\nIS. IK*, under the Act of March 3. 1879.\nPublished every Thursday at Sidney,\nRichland County. Montana.\nSUBSCRIPTION RATES\nRichlind- McKenzie Counties. *3.00 a\nyear; *3 30 a year In Montana: $4.00 a\nyear outside Montana Single copies 10c.\nForeign Countries *5 50\nEDITORIALLY\nON CHRISTMAS TRAVEL\nIt is an unpleasant thought, but\nmore people are killed during the\nChristmas season, travelling home\nfor Christmas and back, than at\nany other time of the year. There\nare a number of reasons for this.\nFor one thing, the Christmas\nholiday season comes at a time\nof the year wdien there is more\ndarkness and less daylight than\nduring any other major holiday\nperiod of the year. For another\nthing the Christmas holiday sea\nson is a long one extending un\ntil after New Year's Day.\nCombined with weather con\nditions, w'hich are often poor, the\nlong nights and the long holi\nday all join to make the Christ\nmas season a deadly one for mo\ntorists and pedestrians alike.\nWe know of several friends\nwho, in recent years, have taken\nto the trains, rather than to the\nhighways, even though they drive\nand might return to their homes\nat Christinas time by car. This\nmay be worth considering for\nthose who are finding driving\nmore\nwho have long distances to drive\nor have cars which are not in\noerfect condition.\nWe remind our readers that\nthis year Americans seem to have\ncut down the death toll on the\nhighways and that unless this\nChristmas is a bloodier one than\ncan be foreseen, 1957 will have\nbeen an improvement over 1956\nin this regard. This is something\nwe ask our readers to keep in\nmind during the remainder of the\nmonth, especially during the fa\n\u2666al days between December 20th\n(a Friday) and January 3rd.\nand more difficult, and\nSATELLITE SNAFU\nAs was predicted,- the decision\nto announce the launching of our\nfirst U. N. satellite, prior to its\nactual launching, was a mis\ntake. Because Defense officials\nwere searching for a counter to\nrecent successful Russian propa\nganda concerning Sputnik II,\nmuch ballyhoo and publicity was\nafforded our first satellite\u2014prior\nto its launening.\nAnd, as feared, snafus develop\ned at the last minute and the\nUnited States was embarrassed\nin the eyes of the world by be\ning unable to fulfill its announce\nment. It will be recalled that the\nRussians made no premature an\nnouncement about what they in\ntended to do prior to the success\nful launching of their satellites.\nAfter they had a satellite circling\nthe earth they announced what\nthey had accomplished, and it was\nan impressive announcement.\nPremature publicity from this\ncountry concerning intentions and\nplans, rather than accomplish\nments, gains us nothing but ridi\ncule, and lays us open for em\n\u25a0f\nSi Cftn\u00f6tma\u00f6 M tety\nMay all your hearts, at Christmastide.\nKnow peace and love and cheer;\nAnd may these precious things abide\nThroughout the coining year.\nRICHLAND\nOf SlONfcY\nRA u DEPOSIT iMiU\nmA\nfj'r A 7 lO'i\nI\nk.NC\nM:\nbarrassment. The Defense Depart\nment and the new Secretary of\nDefense should see to it\nhereafter we blow' our horn about\nwhat w'e have already accom\nplished rather than what we hope\nto do.\nthat\nNEXT MONTH'S WEATHER\nThe United States Weather Bu\nreau in Washington has released\nmaps predicting both the rain or\nsnow and the temperature which\nis likely to prevail in this country\nin the next four weeks, or until\nthe second week in January.\nThose who are interested in pre\ncipitation will be interested to\nj learn that the Eastern half of\nthe United \u00bbStates is expected\nto have more precipitation in the\nthan is\nThe\nform of rain or snow\nnormal for this\nwestern states, including Arizona,\nColorado, most of Wyoming and\nthe w-estern half of Montana, can\nexpect less precipitation than nor\nmal for this time of year.\nA middle belt, extending from\nTexas up through the Dakotas\nwill experience normal precipita\ntion. As for temperature, the east\nern part of the United States can\nexpect higher temperatures than\nusual. A belt to its west, extend\ning into the Dakotas in the north\nand in:o Louisiana in the South,\ncan expect normal temperatures\nfor the next few weeks. East of\nthe mountains on the west coast,\nto Louisiana in the south and\nto the eastern part of the Dakotas,\ntemperatures will be below nor\nmal, and will be much below nor\nmal in most of Texas, Arizona,\nNew Mexico, Nevada, Utah and\nsouthern Wyoming.\nThe west coast itself, and the\ntop of Idaho and western Mon\ntana should experience normal\ntemperatures.\nperiod.\n4,000.000 UNEMPLOYED?\nThe recession, w-hich is being\nargued back and forth by so\nmany economists, is already up\non us. The very fact that the\nGovernment has reduced interest\nrates, in a move to loosen up\nmoney, shows that Washington\nknows it.\nIndustrial production dropped\nto a point in October which is\nthe lowest it has reached since\nJune of 1956. Partly because of\nthis, unemployment is expected to\ntop the 4,000,000 mark in the\nnext few months.\nCompared to this prospect it is\ninteresting to note that the peak\nin unemployment totaled 3,200,000\nlast winter. Despite these and\nother signs, chances are very\ngood that a major recession is not\nin the making.\nWere it not for the fact that\nGovernment spending is expected\nto increase and for other encour\naging signs, such as an increased\nrate of housing starts, the reces\nsion might become severe. This is\ntrue because nothing is being\ndone to solve the farm problem,\nwhich must be settled eventually\nif genuine prosperity is to re\nturn to the country.\nNevertheless, increased Gov\nernment spending, lower interest\nrates and widespread building ac\ntivity, plus other factors, indi\ncate that the recession now un\nderway will not be a prolonged\none. In fact, many economists\nlook for its end late in 1958.\nJudging from the past, the\nevent usually occurs ahead of\nthe forecast. In other words, if\nthe general prediction is for an\nend to the recession late in 1955\nthere is a good chance that the\nrecession will come to an end a\nlittle earlier.\nTRANSLATION\nVOLUNTEERED\nChristian Science Monitor)\nWe have read with delight\nabout the endeavor of the\nCharleston (S. C.) News\nCourier to make that fair city's\n\u2022'perfect English\" intelligible to\nvisiting outlanders. And we ac\ncept the Saturday Evening Post's\nchallenge to do the same for\nBoston.\nThis newspaper has an advan\ntage. It is published in a metro\npolitan hub whose natives, ac\ncording to a local English teach\ner a few years ago, \"have no ac\nBut its editors come from\ncent\nhither and yon. And their ears\nhave not become wholly numbed\nby the accustomed.\nBoston boasts several dialects.\nBut the visitors who wash to ask\ndirections or carry on trade at\nthe town's emporia may find the\nfollowing helpful:\nBann: What fam-ers used to\nkeep horses in.\nKa: What a fam-er keeps in\nliis bann now.\nMorden: What isn't old.\nQtt To: Should.\nPack: To stand a ka out of\n,raffic.\nQuinzy: Birthplace of the na\ntion's sixth President (not what\nyou thought).\nSawr: Past of see.\nSquayah: Center of any town.\nWunt: Will not.\nHaving got lost, you are now\nready for the policeman's re\nsponse to your inquiry how to\nreach the historic Adams home:\nYou Sawr an old white bann\nback theyah? Turn right. That'll\ntake you to Quinzy Squayah.\nTurn again at a morden bank\nbuilding and you ott to be able\nto pack your ka. You warnt get\nlost again.\nIf you've been around here for\na while you'll \"get him\" right\naw'ay; for newcomers it takes a\nlittle longer.\nLAIKA\nG. Rachel Hill\nGreat Falls, Mont\nSince the first shock of Sput\nniks I and II, almost everyone\nhas entered into a gay spirit con\ncerning all the charm bracelets,\nSputnik burgers and other things\nlhat can be commercialized upon\nbecause of the satellite idea. And\nlike making Santa Claus the main\nidea in Christmas, and leaving out\nanything of the sombre or sacri\nficial\u2014the real cataclysmal thing\nthat happened within a spiritual\nerbit has been ignored and\nglossed over.\nI refer to that recipient of one\nof the most Quisling-like incidents\nof which this world can boast\nsince not Pearl Harbor but Gol\ngotha\u2014that little noble, four\nfooted strong-heart they called\nLaika. I don't know what Laika\nthought of her man-god, as she\nwas churned aloft in madness\nt\nu\n.v\ncS\nW.\n\nThe Bel Air 4-Door Sedan-brimming with bold new beaulyl\nCome try the quickest combination on the road!\nCHEVY'S TURBO-THRUST VS\nWITH TURBOGLIDE\nTho Bel Air Impala Sport Coupe\n\u2014one of hvo new super iporf modelsI\n0:0:\n'581\nThere's never been an engine-drive\ncombination like this one! Chevro\nlet's Turbo-Thrust V8* introduces\na radical new slant on engine effi\nciency. The combustion chambers\nare located in the block rather than\nin the head, and chamber surfaces\nare precision machined. The result\nis a wonderfully smooth and even\nflow of power.\nTurboglide*\u2014the other half of the\nteam\u2014is the first and only triple\nturbine automatic drive in Chevy's\nfield. It takes you from a standstill\nthrough cruising in one continuous\nsweep of motion, without even a\nhint of a shift or lag. Harness these\ntriple turbines to a 250-h.p. Turbo\nThrust V8-or the 280-h.p. Super\nTurbo-Thrust*\u2014and you step out\ninstantly in any speed range. Noth\ning else on the road turns your\ntouch into action so quickly, so\nsmoothly. Your Chevrolet dealer\nhas the combination!\nChevrolet*a radical new Turbo\nThrust V8 and honey-smooth\nTurboglide* automatic drive\nform a performance team that\nspells action, 'At all speeds,\nunder all driving conditions,\nthey give you the quickest,\nsmoothest response of any\nthing going.\n\u00e2\u00e2\nfl\n\n\u2022Optional at extra cost.\nBotwAto fioM nnr\nSee Your Local Authorized Chevrolet Dealer\nOnly franchised Chevrolet dealer* display this famous trademark\nY /CHEVROLET /i\nhour after hour, day after day\u2014\neternities roll and I do mean\nroll. No doubt at first within\nthat dark tunnel, she thought\nthat light would presently ap\noear\u2014this monstrous joke, this\nthing gone berserk would right\nitself\u2014she would be freed, praised\nand petted; that her primary\ntask was to hold on, hold on with\nall the endurance and patience\nthat had been intrinsic stuff of\nall her ancestors and of her, her\nself\u2014portrait of all sweetness,\nand to reiterate, nobility.\nAs long as language has made\n\u25a0t possible for man to tell a true\nlegend in drawings, or by word\ncf mouth\u2014the dog and his repu\ntation for faithfulness to his\ngod, humankind, have been ac\nknowledged. Why, then, this\ncolossal betrayal to man's best\nfriend\u2014when rats, mice and other\npestilence abound so much, so\nwell, so everywhere? And why\nbother at this stage whether the\nlikeness to homo-sapiens were\nexactly parallel? My query is\nnot to any particular country, as\n1 realize the ideology exists here\neverywhere.\nThe incident of Laika became\na catalyst which accelerated the\nreaction of people, and found\nthem where they w'ere\u2014split\nthem down the middle\u2014those\nthat didn't give a continental\nand those that did.\nIf the Bible had given specific\nCLARENCE W. SMITH\nAUTHORIZED\nWatkins Dealer\nPhone 772-W 513 71h Si. SX.\n37-tfc\nJERRY'S Market\nGroceries Meats\nSUNDAY HOURS 10 A. M. TO 6 P. M.\nWEEKDAYS 8 A. M. TO 8 P. M.\n323 East Main\nPhone 34\nJERRY ROGERS, Owner\nadmonition to treat animals well,\nfanatic followers of the Law\nwould have made fetishes of\nthem, building baths in the liv\ning room for them, with ser\nvants to brush away the blue\ntail fly\u2014but left to their own de\nvices and their own pithy\nhearts, these same people haven't\nenough warm human blood,\nenough plain compassion for God's\ncreatures than to shrink from\nthem, \"eek\" and \"auk\" at them,\nslam the door in their faces, let\nthem freeze, starve or stray, or\nliterally go to hell as Laika did.\nOften they can smugly gather the\nfamily 'round for evening prayer\nand afterwards blissfully prepare\nfor sleep.\nMany were those who bedded\ndown nights when the Sputniks\nwere lirst aloft and never said\none winging word of prayer for\nLaika. Her torture was nothing to\nthem.\nAccording to Biblical prophesy,\nthe leopard and the lion are go\ning to get along with the lamb,\nand \"a little child shall lead\nthem.\" I don't hear any mention\nof the \"eekers\" and \"aukers\"\u2014\nAttention\nFARMERS\nand\nRANCHERS\nHare Your\nDEAD STOCK\nPicked Upl\nCall\nSidney Rendering Co.\nPHONE NO. 8 COLLECT\nSidney, Montana\nand I could cry blood.\nI wouldn't be surprised to see\nLaika in the crook of the Master's\narm some bright and crystal\nmorning\u2014 Laika, whom mankind\nsaw fit to toss in on a Tower of\nBabel scheme which, seemingly,\nthumbs its nose in the face of\nGod, and hastens the day when\nman will outdistance the speed of\nsound, light, his own conscience\u2014\nto say nothing of the taxpayers\npocketbook. He proposes to show\nGod how to play with Atomic\nbombs, rock the world on its\naxis and ignore economics or\nethics as regards world popula\ntions.\nEverywhere we read of trains\njumping the tracks, accidents, ill\nness and tragedy at every hand.\nCould it be that the Almighty\nft'\n6\n4\n[S\n3 Cfjn\u00f6tma\u00f6 (Mt\nThere's one gift all men can bestow\nThat pleaseth all and God above\nThe richest gift that man doth know\nCosts naught: The gift of selfless love!\nMay the True Christmas Spirit Brighten Your Life\nThis Yuletide\u2014and Through the Coming Year\nSidney National Bank\nSIDNEY. MONTANA\nMEMBER FEDERAL DEPOSIT INSURANCE CORPORATION\nhas taken His protecting hand\nfrom the affairs of men\u2014because\nafter all\u2014they know so much\nand care so little?\nAn intellectual bachelor re\nAdver\nquired for pig farming,\ntised in the London Times.\nNOTICE\nOf Mealing Of\nMASONIC\nFraternities\nfirst and third\n(S)\nTO\nMasonic Lodge\nWednesday.\neastern Star second and fourth\nWednesday.\nRainbow Assembly first and\nthird Tuesday.\nDsMolay Chapter second and\nfourth Tuesday.","height":"22158","width":"16923"}}
